Parliament, Tuesday, 05 June 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services will tomorrow be briefed by the Public Protector on the Public Protector Rules and Policy on the appointment of a Special Advisor to the Executive Authority. The committee will also have discussions on the request to institute an inquiry on the fitness of the Public Protector to hold office. Details are as follows: 
	
	Date: Wednesday, 06 June 2018
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: Old Assembly Chamber, Ground Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES, DR MATHOLE MOTSHEKGA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za The annual Budget determines how much money government departments will receive and has to be approved by Parliament.Read more